Collection of things I learned while developing this website with hugo.

You cant add another param to the menu, it has set params you must use
https://gohugo.io/variables/menus/#readout

You cannot use .Site things in partials but you can use site. 
https://gohugo.io/variables/site/#readout

To determine between a blog post and a regular page (about, contact, etc.) I
made a simple Boolean var in the frontmatter with a corresponding if statment in
the index.html. If the var is true then the post is shown on the home page, otherwise
it is not.
https://github.com/htr3n/hyde-hyde/blob/master/layouts/index.html

I created a "got to top" button by putting the full html code with inline css and js
in the head.html file (which loads on all pages) as a partial
https://www.w3schools.com/howto/howto_js_scroll_to_top.asp
